messages.content: I am baking a pizza, can you help me?
Of course, I'd be happy to help! What do you need assistance with? Do you need a recipe, cooking time and temperature suggestions, topping ideas, or something else?
What temperature should I bake at?

message.content: For a homemade pizza, it's best to bake at a high temperature to achieve a crispy crust. Preheat your oven to 475F (245C). If your oven can go higher and your crust can handle it, you can bake at 500F (260C) for an even crispier result. Make sure to preheat your pizza stone or baking sheet as well if you're using one. How thick is your crust, and what toppings are you using?
